title: The economic cost of Catalonia's independence fight
description: The Spanish prime minister is giving the restive region of Catalonia until Monday, to clarify if it has indeed declared independence. If so, he demands the move be reversed.  Amid the political uncertainty, more companies are leaving Catalonia, raising concerns over the region's economic future.  CGTN's Guy Henderson reports.
